      "explanation": "Requiring management approval for all voids and refunds with immediate notification is the most effective control because it directly addresses the mechanism of the fraud. The scheme relies on the cashier's ability to void legitimate transactions without oversight. Immediate management notification and approval requirements create a contemporaneous review process that makes it difficult for the cashier to complete unauthorized voids. While security cameras (option B) might deter some fraud, they require active monitoring or post-event review to be effective. Random cash counts (option C) might eventually detect shortages but don't prevent the voiding scheme. Requiring two employees (option D) is costly and impractical for most retail operations.",
